goals.question: What is the age distribution of the victims?
goals.rationale: This tells us the age range of the victims and if there is a particular age group that was more affected.

goals.question: What is the gender distribution of the victims?
goals.rationale: This tells us if there is a gender bias in the victims and if one gender was more affected than the other.

goals.question: What is the race distribution of the victims?
goals.rationale: This tells us the racial diversity of the victims and if there is a particular race that was more affected.

goals.question: What is the distribution of incident types that led to the victims' death?
goals.rationale: This tells us the types of incidents that led to the victims' death and if there is a particular incident type that was more common.

goals.question: What is the geographical distribution of the incidents?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of longitude and latitude
goals.rationale: This tells us the locations where the incidents occurred and if there is a particular area that was more affected.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', bins=20)
    plt.title("What is the age distribution of the victims?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='gender', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the victims?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(race_counts, labels=race_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the race distribution of the victims?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
